cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it addresses the problem of semantic correspondence between images. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of synthetic geometric deformations and the differentiable version of the argmax function could also suggest that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) categories.
